  "title": "Audit Semi-Seniors",
  "description": "<p><strong>Company Overview / Employee Value Proposition</strong></p><p>Genuine CA PAC is a public accounting firm providing a comprehensive full range of professional services to our clients based locally and overseas in a variety of industries</p><p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>Lead and execute audit assignments for SMEs, delivering accurate financial statements and tax computations while ensuring compliance with statutory requirements and contributing to the firm’s audit excellence.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Develop and execute detailed audit plans, including system reviews and audit fieldwork, to ensure compliance and accuracy in financial reporting for SMEs</li><li>Prepare audited and unaudited financial statements that meet regulatory filing requirements and support client business needs</li><li>Calculate corporate tax liabilities by preparing precise tax computations for timely corporate tax filings</li><li>Collaborate effectively with clients and internal teams to communicate audit findings and resolve issues at all organizational levels</li><li>Manage ad hoc audit and administrative tasks to support audit team operations and client service delivery</li><li>Apply independent judgment and teamwork skills to deliver audit assignments with diligence and professionalism</li></ul><p><strong>Required competencies and certifications</strong></p><ul><li>Minimum of 2 years of audit experience</li><li>Degree in Accountancy, ACCA, or equivalent professional qualification</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Proficient in Microsoft Word and Excel to prepare audit documentation and reports</li><li>Strong interpersonal and communication skills to engage with diverse stakeholders and facilitate audit processes</li></ul>",
